## Step 2: Calculate the percentage of patients with normal blood pressure
To find the percentage of patients with normal blood pressure, we subtract the sum of percentages of patients with high and low blood pressure from 100%. So, percentage with normal blood pressure = 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.

