To find the percentage of patients with regular heartbeat and low blood pressure, we first note that 19% have low blood pressure. We then subtract the percentage of patients with low blood pressure and irregular heartbeat from the total percentage with low blood pressure. So, percentage with regular heartbeat and low blood pressure = 19% - 3.9% = 15.1%.

