Solution: ## Step 1
To find $P\left(A_1 \cup A_2 \cup A_3\right)$, we need to apply Theorem 1.1-6, which states that for any events $A$, $B$, and $C$, $P(A \cup B \cup C) = P(A) + P(B) + P(C) - P(A \cap B) - P(A \cap C) - P(B \cap C) + P(A \cap B \cap C)$.

